value.0: Gren was the purveyor of textiles, fine cloth and other sundries in the Lockwood Hamlet.
The jambiya is a hooked dagger worn by almost all Calishite men. Calishites seem to favor curved blades in general.
These cotton covered sacks of down provide a somewhat comfortable place to rest ones head.

While the bed itself is of average quality, the canopy which drapes over it is made from a quality wool made right here in Tethyr.  While much  of the year is warm, canopies such as these were staples for noble families during the winter.  Small stones sewn into the bottom hems kept the sides from shifting too much when winter winds would draft under doors or through open windows.
Imported from the city of Amnwater in nearby Amn, carpets of exotic animals and designs are sought after by those of modest wealth.

A luxury piece of silken fabric with golden hues, this table covering is ideal for more high end costomers.  The delicate nature of the fabric make it impractical for regular use, but ideal for ceremonies or events where one wishes to flaunt their wealth.

This old oil painting depicts a man with noble bearing and a clear mixture of Tethyrian and Calishite heritage. A gold plaque at the bottom of the painting declares the man: "Lord Tiberius Arundel - 1020 DR."
The scene printed upon this tapestry depicts a royal family preparing for a hunt.  Printed on challis, a lightweight, soft plain weave cotton with a slightly brushed surface.
Sturdy cotton cloth with fancy gold threads stitched into patterns.
A simple design, this well oiled, heavy, woven bit of fabric is draped over a simple wooden frame to provide shelter from light winds and rain out in the wilds.
The bottom of this bedroll consists of several layers, including oilcloth, woven straw, and cotton fabric to provide a more comfortable nights sleep in the wilds, at the cost of slightly more weight.
Numerous banners line the wall depicting the variety of styles available to those seeking to start their own guild or company.  All are made of durable cloth with vibrant colored dyes.
A display with assorted cloaks of various style, design, and quality.

There are a number of silk flowers in a variety of styles and colors for fashioning  lasting bouquet, decorating your hat, or simply making arrangements that you don't need to water to decorate your home.
These exotic dyes are imported from around Faerun.
Exotic Finery from far away Kara-Tur and Maztica
This versatile kit contains the various dyes needed to customize clothing.
This small crystal bead might be used in simple jewelry.
This is a patch of cured leather which might have some esoteric use.
This is a sewing kit with several steel useful parts needed to repair items of various sorts. It looks like it takes some skill to make the best use of.
